                <Value>Condition</Value>
                <Children>
                  <LocaleResource Name="Description">
                    <Value>
                      With conditions you can filter the products for which this attachment will be shown.&lt;br/&gt;
                      The conditions consist of &lt;strong&gt;Condition Groups&lt;/strong&gt;. &lt;br/&gt;
                      The &lt;strong&gt;Default State&lt;/strong&gt; is also considered as a condition group. &lt;br/&gt;
                      A Condition Group consists of one or many &lt;strong&gt;Condition Statements&lt;/strong&gt; (rules).&lt;br/&gt;
                      The dependancy between the Condition Groups is &lt;strong&gt;OR&lt;/strong&gt; and between the Condition Statements is &lt;strong&gt;AND&lt;/strong&gt;. This means that if all of the Condition Statements in one Condition Group are true for a product, the attachment will be displayed over that product.&lt;br/&gt;
                      To add a Condition Group you need to click on the &lt;strong&gt;Add Condition Group&lt;/strong&gt; button.
                      To delete a Condition Group you need to click on the &lt;strong&gt;Delete&lt;/strong&gt; button.
                      To add a Condition Statement to the Condition Group, you need to click on the &lt;strong&gt;Add new record&lt;/strong&gt; button.
                    </Value>
                  </LocaleResource>
